text.section:
Funds in the Tidal Wetlands Compensation Fund may be appropriated only for the creation, restoration, or enhancement of tidal wetlands, including:
Acquisition of land or easements;
Maintenance of mitigation sites;
Purchase of credits in mitigation banks;
Management of invasive or nuisance species identified by the Department;
Cost sharing assistance to landowners in the management and control of phragmites under Title 8, Subtitle 21 of the Natural Resources Article; and
Contractual services necessary to accomplish the intent of this subsection.
